                    <lb n="1"/><w lemma="ἰσόψηφος">ἰσόψηφα</w>
                    <lb n="2"/><w lemma="κύριος">κύριος</w> ω
                    <lb n="3"/><w lemma="πίστις">πίστις</w> ω
                </ab>
            </div>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <ab>1. Artemidoros is among the most popular names at Smyrna, as one can see from LGPN 5A.71, where it occupies nearly a column.<lb/>
                    4–5. Both <w lemma="κύριος">κύριος</w> (20 + 400 + 100 + 10 + 70 + 200) and <w lemma="πίστις">πίστις</w> (80 + 10 + 200 + 300 + 10 + 200) in fact add up to 800 as isopsephisms. For the Christian character of the inscription, see Bagnall, R., Everyday Writing in the Graeco-Roman East (2011): 45.</ab>
            </div> 
